(%i3) subst ([sheep = 3*goat, horse = 10*goat], baz);
(%o3)                       27 ` goat
(%i4) baz2 : 1000`gallon/fortnight;
                                gallon
(%o4)                   1000 ` ---------
                               fortnight
(%i5) subst (fortnight = 14*day, baz2);
                          500   gallon
(%o5)                     --- ` ------
                           7     day
@end example

Arithmetic operations on dimensional quantities.

@c ===beg===
@c load (ezunits)$
@c 100 ` kg + 200 ` kg;
@c 100 ` m^3 - 100 ` m^3;
@c (10 ` kg) * (17 ` m/s^2);
@c (x ` m) / (y ` s);
@c (a ` m)^2;
@c ===end===
